    "ragtruth_id": "943",
    "text": "Desperate migrants, mostly from Africa and the Middle East, continue to make the dangerous journey to Europe. Over 978 migrants were rescued in the Mediterranean Sea off the coast of Libya. Italy has seen over 10,000 migrants arrive in the first three months of 2015, with at least 2,000 rescued in the first weekend of April. The majority of migrants come from West Africa, Somalia, and Syria, using Libya as a transit country. Tragically, at least 480 migrants have died crossing the Mediterranean this year, often due to bad weather and overcrowded vessels. Last year at this time, there were fewer than 50 reported deaths. The migrants include asylum seekers, victims of trafficking or violence, unaccompanied children, and pregnant women.",
